Balance Query & Transfers
Last updated December 23rd, 2025

Overview
The Hubtel Balance Query API allows you to check the balances of both POS Sales and Prepaid Deposit accounts associated with your Hubtel Merchant Account.

The Hubtel Balance Query API facilitates the transfer of funds from your POS Sales account to your Prepaid Deposit account within your Hubtel Merchant Account.

You can find your POS SALES and PREPAID DEPOSIT IDs here.


Getting Started

Business IP Whitelisting
You must share your public IP address with your Retail System Engineer for whitelisting.

bulb-icon
Note
All API Endpoints are live and only requests from whitelisted IP(s) can reach the endpoints shared in this reference.

API Reference
The Hubtel Balance Query And Transfer API focuses on:

Balance Query
Balance Transfer

Balance Query

POS Sales Balance Query
This endpoint can be used to query the balance of your POS Sales account.

To initiate a request, send an HTTP GET request to the below URL with the required parameters. Passing your Hubtel POS Sales ID in the endpoint is mandatory. Find your POS Sales ID here.

API Endpoint	https://trnf.hubtel.com/api/inter-transfers/{POS_SALES_ID}
Request Type	GET
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
POS_SALES_ID	Number	Mandatory	The merchant's Hubtel POS Sales ID. Find yours here.

SAMPLE POS SALES BALANCE QUERY REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
  GET api/inter-transfers/11684 HTTP/1.1
  Host: trnf.hubtel.com
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Basic endjeOBiZa250fT3=
  Cache-Control: no-cache

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
responseCode	String	The unique response code on the status of the request
message	String	The status of the request
data	Object	An object containing the required data response from the POS Sales Balance Query API.
amount	Float	The balance of the account queried

SAMPLE SERVER RESPONSE
200 OK

copy
Copy
  {
    "responseCode": "0000",
    "message": "Success",
    "data": {
        "amount": 123.50
    }
  }

Prepaid Deposit Balance Query
This endpoint can be used to query the balance of your Prepaid Deposit account.

To initiate a request, send an HTTP GET request to the below URL with the required parameters. Passing your Hubtel Prepaid Deposit ID in the endpoint is mandatory. Find your Prepaid Deposit ID here.

API Endpoint	https://trnf.hubtel.com/api/inter-transfers/prepaid/{PREPAID_DEPOSIT_ID}
Request Type	GET
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
PREPAID_DEPOSIT_ID	Number	Mandatory	The merchant's Hubtel Prepaid Deposit ID. Find yours here.

