Balance Transfer
This endpoint allows you to transfer funds from your POS Sales account to your Prepaid Deposit account within your Hubtel Merchant Account. To initiate a Balance Transfer request, send an HTTP POST request to the below URL with the required parameters. Passing your POS Sales ID in the endpoint is also mandatory. Find your POS Sales ID here.


API Endpoint	https://trnf.hubtel.com/api/inter-transfers/{POS_SALES_ID}
Request Type	POST
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
POS_SALES_ID	Float	Mandatory	The merchant's Hubtel POS Sales ID. Find yours here.
Description	String	Mandatory	A brief desciption of the transaction
Amount	Float	Mandatory	The amount to be sent from the account specified e.g. 0.50
ClientReference	String	Mandatory	The reference provided by the API user, and must be unique and preferably be alphanumeric characters. Maximum length is 36 characters
DestinationAccountNumber	String	Mandatory	The account you are transferring to, i.e., the Prepaid Deposit ID. Find yours here.
PrimaryCallbackUrl	String	Mandatory	URL used to receive callback payload of Balance Transfer transactions from Hubtel.

SAMPLE BALANCE TRANSFER REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
  GET api/inter-transfers/11684 HTTP/1.1
  Host: trnf.hubtel.com
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Basic endjeOBiZa250fT3=
  Cache-Control: no-cache

  {
    "Description": "Hubtel Transfer Test", 
    "Amount": 0.8,
    "ClientReference": "bd0io3202ef49", 
    "DestinationAccountNumber": "11691",
    "PrimaryCallbackUrl": "https://webhook.site/b513d1a9-e7826-a6ede",
  }

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
responseCode	String	The unique response code on the status of the request
message	String	The status of the request
data	Object	An object containing the required data response from the Hubtel Balance Transefer API.
clientReference	String	The reference provided by the API user
amount	Float	The amount sent from the account specified
charges	Float	The amount charged. There is no charge. It is free
meta	String	This is usually null
recipientName	String	The name on the merchant account

SAMPLE SERVER RESPONSE
200 OK

copy
Copy
{ 
  "responseCode": "0001", 
  "message": "Pending", 
  "data": {
    "clientReference": "bd0i03202ef49",
    "description": "Your request has been accepted. We'll notify you when the transaction is completed.",
    "amount": 0.8, 
    "charges": 0, 
    "meta": null,
    "recipientName": "gershon" 
  }
}

Transfer Callback
The Hubtel Balance Transfer API mandatorily sends a payload to callbackURL provided in each request. The callback payload determines final status of a pending transaction response i.e. transaction with 0000 ResponseCode. The callback URL you specified in the Balance Transfer request should be implemented to listen for a HTTP POST payload from Hubtel. Hubtel Balance Transfer has an asynchronous flow.

This means that the final status of a transaction cannot be determined immediately after a request. It may take some time (usually less than 30 seconds). Hence, it is paramount and required to implement an HTTP callback on your server to be able to receive the final status of each transaction.


SAMPLE BALANCE TRANSFER CALLBACK
200 OK

copy
Copy
{
  "ResponseCode": "0000", 
  "Message": "Success", 
  "Data": { 
      "ClientReference": "b03202ef49", 
      "Description": "Hubtel Transfer Test", 
      "Amount": 0.8,
      "Charges": null, 
      "Meta": null,
      "RecipientName": "gershon", 
  }
}

Transfer Status Check
It is mandatory to implement the Balance Transfer Status Check API as it allows merchants to check for the status of a balance transfer in rare instances where a merchant does not receive the final status of the transfer from Hubtel after five (5) minutes.

To check the status of a transfer, send an HTTP GET request to the below URL, with either one or more unique transaction identifiers as parameters.

It is also mandatory to pass your POS Sales ID for Status Check requests in the endpoint. Find your POS Sales ID here.


API Endpoint	https://trnf.hubtel.com/api/inter-transfers/status/{POS_Sales_ID}?clientReference=xxxxxxxxx
Request Type	GET
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
clientReference	String	Mandatory	The client reference of the transaction specified in the request payload.

SAMPLE REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
GET /api/inter-transfers/status/11684?clientReference=76576343905406557 HTTP/1.1
Host: trnf.hubtel.com
Authorization: Basic QmdfaWjkjJhc2U29lbmNvmkGUoa2hzcW9seXU6bXVhaHdpYW8pfQ==

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
message	String	The description of response received from the API that is related to the ResponseCode.
responseCode	String	The response code of the API after the request.
data	Object	An object containing the required data response from the API.
id	String	The unique ID used to identify a Hubtel transaction (from Hubtel).
createdAt	String	Date of the transaction.
updatedAt	String	Date the transaction was updated. Default value: null.
transferDescription	String	The initial description passed.
transferAmount	Float	Amount transferred.
clientReference	String	The reference ID that is initially provided by the client/API user in the request payload (from merchant).
callbackUrl	String	The initial callbackUrl passed.
fromAccountType	String	The originating account for the transfer.
fromAccountId	String	The account number of the origination account i.e.: POS Sales ID
toAccountType	String	The destination account for the transfer.
toAccountId	String	The account number of the destination account i.e.: Prepaid Deposit ID
fromBusinessId	String	The business ID of the merchant.
toBusinessId	String	The business ID of the merchant.
status	String	Status of the transaction i.e.: success or failed.
failureReason	String	Reason for the transfer failure; could be null.

SAMPLE RESPONSE (Successful)
200 OK

copy
Copy
{
  "message": "success",
  "code": "200",
  "data": {
      "id": "bfe03a54f40e4f91ae8d1977f2250d39",
      "createdAt": "2024-07-03T16:48:49.1073714+00:00",
      "updatedAt": null,
